Description: Body sherd (mended from two fragments) of Milesian Pre-Fikellura pottery closed vessel, krater or amphora; white slip; exterior: reserved except for two painted light orange dots; inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Old glue on upper left edge shows a join to this fragment of a sherd noted on index card as not yet found in 1965. The sherd possibly comes from the same vase as British Museum 1886,0401.89. There is a modern inscription, giving Petrie's catalogue numbers, written in ink '332' and '333' on the exterior of the sherd.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, nos 332-3)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 671, no. 294)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.037)
